hands_on_practices.solution:
We wish to compute 
$$g_F \approx g_J\,\frac{F(F+1)+J(J+1)-I(I+1)}{2\,F(F+1)}$$ 
for the upper hyperfine level $F=I+J$ of $^{87}\mathrm{Rb}$ in the ground state $^2S_{1/2}$ (so $L=0$, $S=\tfrac12$, $J=\tfrac12$, $I=\tfrac32$).  

1. Compute $g_J$ from  
$$g_J \;=\; g_L\,\frac{J(J+1)+L(L+1)-S(S+1)}{2J(J+1)}
\;+\;g_S\,\frac{J(J+1)-L(L+1)+S(S+1)}{2J(J+1)}$$  
with $g_L=1$, $g_S=2$, $L=0$, $S=\tfrac12$, $J=\tfrac12$.  Note  
$$J(J+1)=\tfrac12\bigl(\tfrac12+1\bigr)=\tfrac34,\quad
L(L+1)=0,\quad S(S+1)=\tfrac34.$$  
Hence  
$$g_J
=1\cdot\frac{\tfrac34+0-\tfrac34}{2\cdot\tfrac34}
+2\cdot\frac{\tfrac34-0+\tfrac34}{2\cdot\tfrac34}
=0+2\cdot\frac{\tfrac32}{\tfrac32}
=2.$$  

2. For the upper hyperfine level $F=I+J=\tfrac32+\tfrac12=2$, we have  
$$F(F+1)=2\cdot3=6,\quad J(J+1)=\tfrac34,\quad I(I+1)=\tfrac32\bigl(\tfrac32+1\bigr)=\tfrac{15}{4}.$$  
Then the numerator in $g_F$ is  
$$F(F+1)+J(J+1)-I(I+1)
=6+\tfrac34-\tfrac{15}{4}
=6-\tfrac{12}{4}
=6-3=3.$$  
Thus  
$$g_F \approx 2\;\frac{3}{2\cdot6}
=\frac{6}{12}
=\frac12.$$
